curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/1372' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM6130", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM6130 is a current-mode step-down regulator  with an internal power MOSFET. This device has a  fixed switching frequency of 385kHz. It can efficiently  provide up to 3A output load current over a wide input  supply range from 4.5V to 28.5V with good load and  line regulations responses.   In addition, the SGM6130 is highly efficient with peak  efficiency at 94% when in operation. The shutdown  supply current consumed by the regulator is less than  18µA. Protection features include cycle-by-cycle  current limit and thermal shutdown. The device also  includes an internal soft-start and an external  adjustable soft-start function to limit the inrush current  and prevent the overshoot of output voltage.   The SGM6130 is available in a Green SOIC-8  (Exposed Pad) package and also minimizes the  external components of the device to complete a 3A  buck DC/DC converter solution.  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/1373' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM6130", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● 4.5V to 28.5V Input Voltage Range  ● 0.8V to 25V Adjustable Output Voltage Range   ● 3A Output Current  ● 94% Peak Efficiency   ● Shutdown Supply Current: 18µA (MAX)  ● 100mΩ Internal Power MOSFET Switch  ● 385kHz Fixed Switching Frequency  ● Under-Voltage Lockout  ● Cycle-by-Cycle Current Limit  ● Thermal Shutdown  ● Support Low ESR Ceramic Capacitors   ● -40℃ to +85℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in a Green SOIC-8 (Exposed Pad) Package      "}'
